<br>
It all really depends on what you are fighting.  If you opt to fight mid to high blue cons (or higher) an extra mob at the wrong time is sure death or a trip to the nearest zone.  If you are fighting low blues (where you don't have to burn a ton of mana to kill it) then you can do 2 fairly easily.<br>
<br>
If your channeling is good and you get an extra mob on you just stand there and burn down the first one that the pet is fighting as fast as you can.  Once the first is dead your pet will come and save you and either give you a chance to run or a chance to kill mob #2.<br>
<br>
My advice - know the level of the things you are fighting and know the level of the things that are liable to jump in on you.  Have a preset plan so you can make that split second decision whether to fight or run.  Any hesitation can cause a nice jaunt back to your corpse.<br>
